        <p class="paragraph">
            Wool is sensitive to temperature and humidity fluctuations. 
            Warehouses should be equipped with climate control systems to maintain stable conditions. 
            Ideal storage conditions typically range from 50-65°F (10-18°C) and 45-55% relative humidity.
            temperature and humidity control in wool storage warehouses are vital to safeguarding this valuable natural resource. 
            By adhering to the recommended temperature and humidity ranges, farmers and warehouse operators can ensure that their wool inventory remains in optimal condition, 
            free from damage caused by moisture, temperature fluctuations, and pests, thereby maximizing its value and utility.
        </p>
